# No Em Dashes

Never use em dashes (the long dash character) in any text you write for this project.

This applies to:
- UI copy and labels
- Markdown blog posts and project write-ups
- Code comments
- Documentation
- Commit messages
- Data strings in portfolio.ts and similar files

Use these alternatives instead:
- Colons: "Vizion: a text-to-animation tool"
- Commas: "React, TypeScript, and Tailwind"
- Parentheses: "Nest (in closed testing)"
- Separate sentences

Before finishing any task, scan your written text for em dashes and replace them.
